<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Microsoft support group busy with Windows 98 questions
 &HT;    By Yusuf Davis
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Why can't I get this scanner to work? Where is that mouse
cursor? What's wrong with this danged thing? Those are just a few
of the questions Windows 98 users are asking that can be reproduced
in a family newspaper.
</P>
<P>
   Two weeks after launching the latest upgrade to the world's most
popular operating system, the customer support people are busy.
</P>
<P>
   Despite a huge number of enhancements, upgraded drivers and
user-friendly features, some users are still baffled, even by the
installation of the software. But many problems can be corrected
with technical support available online at the Microsoft Web site
(http:
</P>
</TEXT>
