_ Abbott Laboratories, Hoechst, Pharmacia and Upjohn and
Rhone-Poulenc _ have tentatively agreed to pay about $350 million
to settle class-action price-fixing litigation brought against the
drug industry by thousands of independent pharmacies and drugstore
chains.
