McDowell.
</P>
<P>
   SAFRICA-ECON (Johannesburg) _ Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin
holds talks with South African business leaders and government
officials. With the rand tumbling and gold prices low, the
government has adopted a conservative, budget-cutting economic
strategy. The United States likes the policy _ but the South
African government hates to be seen doing anything that pleases the
United States.
</P>
