fattest bank account _ with $220 billion in cash on hand -- more
than $1 trillion in overseas holdings and an industrious,
well-educated workforce that is the world's most efficient at
turning out automobiles, electronic gear and sophisticated
industrial machinery? Japan, the same country now being fingered by
the United States, and others for courting a global recession. A
look at the underlying strengths of Japan's economy, it's
breathtaking fall from grace and a plausible road out. (Deans, Cox
News Service).
