<HEADLINE>
A PRODUCT-BY-PRODUCT LOOK AT INSECT REPELLENTS
</HEADLINE>
 (EDS: Accompanies INSECT REPELLENTS) 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Product: Blocker
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 2 percent soybean oil
</P>
<P>
   The hype: DEET-free!
</P>
<P>
   Notable: More than 97 percent protective in Canadian field
tests; may be the best of herbal products. Smells like soap; burns
eyes and lips.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: Skin-So-Soft; Suncare Plus; Bug Guard
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: .01 to .05 percent citronella
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Mild woodland or herbal scent is pleasing to people,
offensive to mosquitoes.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Basically, these are offshoots of a popular Avon bath
oil that fans claim repels bugs; but beware of repellents sold
door-to-door.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: OFF!
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 15 percent DEET
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Famous orange can, fresh outdoor fragrance.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: You've probably used this one for years. Remember, it's
harmful if swallowed; avoid contact with eyes, as well as plastics,
furniture finishes, watch crystals.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: OFF! Mosquito Coil
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: .10 percent d/l-allethrolone d-trans
chrysanthemate (Permethrin)
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Yard and garden insect control with country fresh
scent.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: A ``knockdown'' insecticide that actually kills
mosquitoes. Beware of active ingredient with that many letters.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: OFF! Citronella Candle
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 3.06 percent citronella
</P>
<P>
   The hype: ``Vanilla Breezes'' mask the citronella smell.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Protects outdoors, but ordinary candles work almost as
well.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: OFF! Deep Woods
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 20 percent DEET
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Top-selling repellent in the United States with SPF 15
sunscreen. Sportsmen swear by it.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Harmful if swallowed, irritating to eyes, repellent may
make sunscreen slightly less effective.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: Banana Boat Bite Block and Bite Block for Children
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 10 percent DEET
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Repels mosquitoes, ticks, chiggers, gnats, fleas and
biting flies.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Repellent may reduce effectiveness of sunscreen in
combination products. Watch out for spandex swimsuits. Do not apply
to sunburned skin.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: Mosquito Torpedo
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredients: citronella, cedarwood, witch hazel
(concentrations not available on product label)
</P>
<P>
   The hype: ``Nature's insect repellent.''
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Safe for the whole family _ except those who are
allergic to it. Can burn the eyes.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: BugChaser bracelet
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredients: 4.015 percent d-Limonene, .024 percent
Dihydro-5-pentyl-2(3H) furanone, and .049 percent
Dihydro-5-heptyl-2(3H) furanone
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Smells like lemons; a 1996-97 National Mail Order
Association Top 500 Winner; made with FDA-approved food additives.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Should you trust a product that is this complex?
Besides, do you want to wear bug-chasing jewelry?
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: Buzz Away
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredients: 5 percent citronella, also essential oils of
cedarwood, eucalyptus, lemongrass amd peppermint
</P>
<P>
   The hype: ``Nature's solution'' to repel mosquitoes, gnats,
black flies and no-see-ums.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Hourly application may be necessary for protection. May
cause substantial but temporary eye injury.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: REPEL 100
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 100 percent DEET
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Protects for up to 10 hours against severe
infestation.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Do not spray in enclosed areas; wash treated skin with
soap and water when returning indoors.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: REPEL Insect Block
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 29 percent DEET
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Sportsman formula for active outdoors men and women;
provides hours of effective protection.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Do not apply over cuts, wounds or irritated skin or to
hands of young children. Flammable, may damage furniture finish,
plastics, acetate, rayon, spandex.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: Natrapel
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 10 percent citronella
</P>
<P>
   The hype: A pleasant, effective alternative to DEET.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Mild, refreshing scent. Apply every two to three hours,
more often if needed. Avoid contact with eyes.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: Cutter
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 7 percent DEET
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Pleasant protection. Makes you invisible to bugs.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Contains aloe and vitamin E as a bonus; fresh, mild
scent.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: Skintastic, Skintastic for Kids
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredient: 7 to 10 percent DEET
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Nongreasy, pleasantly scented for up to two hours'
protection. Ideal for the park or back yard.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Spray or lotion has aloe vera, comes with or without
sunscreen. Another OFF! product.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Product: Sawyer Gold Composite
</P>
<P>
   Active ingredients: 17.5 percent DEET, 5 percent N-octyl
bicycloheptene dicarboximide and 2.5 percent Di-n-propyl
isocinchomeronate
</P>
<P>
   The hype: Combo that repels deer flies and stable flies as well
as black flies, ticks, mosquitoes, chiggers and gnats.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: With all that, it ``ought'' to repel everything.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   SOURCES: product labels
</P>
