position to compete for advertising time and space with incumbent
U.S. Rep. Charlie Norwood. Williams
</P>
<P>
   MAINE -- SALMON. Maine's salmon industry scored a major victory
Tuesday as the International Trade Commission left intact duties
against the largest importers of Chilean salmon. In a 2-1 vote, the
ITC determined that Maine's salmon farmers had been financially
injured by Chile's salmon companies, which, the U.S. Commerce
Department says, have been dumping their product on the U.S. market
at below-market prices. Kane
</P>
