DeWine's crime proposals: the Crime Identification Technology Act
and the Crime Victims with Disabilities Awareness Act. Talking to
Ohio State Police. Baker &AMP; Baker
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH CAROLINA -- BOSNIA. U.S. Rep. Lindsey Graham, back from a
trip to Bosnia, is concerned about continued congressional funding
of the U.S military presence there. (Possible.) Williams
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS -- ORTIZ. Rep. Solomon Ortiz, who has returned from his
trip to Bosnia, believes the troops there are operating with a
skeletal force and that it shouldn't be cut any more. He also
believes that the way soldiers are stationed there must be changed,
because some are forced to choose between their families and the
military. Marlin
</P>
<P>
   -- BEACHES. Texas is doing a poor job of monitoring the water
quality of its beaches and of informing the public of any
pollution. Barton
</P>
<P>
