A4367 &Cx1f; taf-z
u d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-WINE-TASTINGS-NYT &LR;      07-14 0138
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WINE-TASTINGS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SALVIANO ORVIETO CLASSICO 1996, UMBRIA, ITALY. ABOUT $12. 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Italy leads the world in the production of top quality wines at
moderate prices, as this exceptional Orvieto readily attests.
Orvieto, an hour's drive north of Rome, is a delightful small city,
which gives its name to one of Italy's best-known white wines.
</P>
<P>
   The prescribed formula for Orvieto permits a wide choice of
grapes in the blend, but the base wine is invariably the dull
trebbiano. The Tenuta di Salviano estate rescues this wine, of
which about 40 percent is trebbiano, by adding verdello, grechetto,
chardonnay, sauvignon blanc, malvasia and drupeggio _ a new one to
me. The result is a golden, fragrant, surprisingly complex wine to
go with Italian cheese and seafood.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
