<SLUG> BC-BOHLS-COLUMN15-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   Some suggestions for the new baseball commissioner
</P>
<P>
   By Kirk Bohls
</P>
<P>
   Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   So, after enduring years of cajoling and arm-twisting, Bud Selig
finally relented and became baseball commissioner. He reluctantly
agreed to take a $3 million position, a fancy office, limo service,
lavish expense account, etc. Hate to think what he'd have gotten if
he had wanted the job.
</P>
<P>
   Now Selig has been on the job for a while, and the biggest news
out of his office was a statement saying baseball has no bigger fan
than Bud Selig.
</P>
<P>
   Hey, thanks, Buddy boy, but there's a bit more on your plate
than root-root- rooting for the home team. So get your feet off the
desk. Assuming Fay Vincent didn't leave this in the top drawer
before you and your cronies ran him off, here's an updated
commissioner to-do list to save baseball:
</P>
<P>
   _ Demote all umpires who won't call a strike a strike.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fine players who don't run out ground balls.
</P>
<P>
   _ Surgically implant some humility in J.D. Drew.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make players stand in the hot dog line once a week.
</P>
<P>
   _ Show Ken Griffey Jr. the right way to wear a cap.
</P>
<P>
   _ Find someone like Billy Martin to instill some life into these
cookie- cutout managers.
</P>
<P>
   _ Take away players' post-game buffet spreads. Make 'em wait in
the McDonald's drive-through lane same as we do.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make George Steinbrenner live in New Jersey if he wants to
move his team there so badly.
</P>
<P>
   _ Give the players two three-day breaks during the season so
they can still identify their wives and kids. What is the divorce
rate for ballplayers anyway?
</P>
<P>
   _ Prevail upon your once-fellow owners to stop the lip service
and reduce ticket prices from the average cost of $13.60.
</P>
<P>
   _ Insist all players take a nickname like Hack Wilson.
</P>
<P>
   _ Find a closer for the Atlanta Braves.
</P>
<P>
   _ Find a bullpen for the Seattle Mariners.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make John Kruk international ambassador to baseball. Better
yet, make him a TV color guy.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sue the pants off Mike Ditka if he ever threatens to sing
``Take Me Out To The Ball Game'' again.
</P>
<P>
   _ Punch out any sportscaster who leads off with ``Mark McGwire
went homerless again for the second game in a row.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Bring back Earl Weaver and his tomato plants.
</P>
<P>
   _ Investigate why Mike Piazza has not been traded in a month.
</P>
<P>
   _ Officially change the name to the fair pole.
</P>
<P>
   _ Pool the talent on the Expos, Pirates and A's and put the
franchise in Wichita Falls, the new sports capital of the USA.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hook Tommy Lasorda and Bill Russell up to a polygraph machine.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tar and feather the next owner to sell the naming rights of
his new stadium to Bob's Rattlesnake Farm.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fine Jim Leyland for not putting Kerry Wood on the NL All-Star
team. What is it about marketing that the Marlins manager does not
understand?
</P>
<P>
   _ Give Barry Bonds a personality transplant.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make ESPN quit airing those inane Netboy spots. (And tell 'em
Jose Cruz Jr. isn't even in the majors anymore.)
</P>
<P>
   _ Get Ken Burns to do a retrospective on Jeff Maier.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cut off at the knees any player who balks at a new contract
and spouts off, ``It isn't about the money.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Keep Pete Rose out of the Hall of Fame until he admits his
sins.
</P>
<P>
   _ Get Kenneth Starr to investigate why anyone goes to Florida
Marlins games.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hire hit men to take out any sports columnist suggesting Cal
Ripken Jr. take a day off.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hire a hair stylist for Randy Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   _ If you won't abolish the DH, sponsor a ``Take a DH to Lunch''
program so he's not so misunderstood.
</P>
<P>
   _ Send a group of All-Stars around the country to
non-major-league cities in the off-season in a massive meet the
players campaign and _ I know this is outrageous stuff _ do not
charge for autographs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Investigate to see if the White Sox have a manager. Or a team.
</P>
<P>
   _ Get Jim Thome a sock contract.
</P>
<P>
   _ Clone Ben Grieve and Nomar Garciaparra.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bring back Dizzy Dean and Pee Wee.
</P>
<P>
   _ Give Darryl Kile a clue.
</P>
<P>
   _ Force the Rangers to trade their entire AAA team for Randy
Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make the players pay a salary surcharge _ say, $50,000 per $1
million _ to help pay their share for new stadiums.
</P>
<P>
   _ If Mark McGwire hits 62 homers, next year let pitchers throw a
wiffle ball at him.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bring back that hokey Home Run Derby.
</P>
<P>
   _ Do not expand for 50 years.
</P>
<P>
   _ Give Tony Phillips one free ``Get out of Jail'' card.
</P>
<P>
   _ Keep interleague play, but make sure the Rangers play the
Astros.
</P>
<P>
   _ Work on throwing out the first pitch. That was lame.
</P>
<P>
   _ Get a real job. As commissioner, you will be nothing more than
a walking, talking _ OK, lip-synching _ puppet of the owners.
</P>
<P>
   Kirk Bohls' column appears in the Austin American-Statesman,
Austin, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
