Johnson filed an on-air apology retracting the report for lack of
evidence to support its claims. Since then, the walls have shaken
at the Atlanta-based network, considered one of the most-watched _
and most-credible _ news operations in the world. But that shake-up
doesn't compare with the credibility whipping it has been taking at
