(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Bob
McCarthy at the Daily News, (818) 713-3665. 
. 
ABOUT-MARY (Los Angeles) _ The makers of Dumb and Dumber have
become gross and grosser with ``There's Something About Mary,'' an
R-rated comedy (a rarity these days) that smashes taboos with glee.
We talk to the Bobby and Peter Farrelly and find out what's going
on inside their twisted minds. By Glenn Whipp. 
. 
MARY-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ ``There's Something About Mary'' calls
to mind the spirit of Brooks and Monty Python and ``Animal House''
in its manic zeal to milk every sacred cow in the name of facetious
fun. You'll laugh. You'll groan. Often at the same time. Yet, this
is the most consistently funny movie the Farrelly brothers have
made. 

