<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Braves ondeck: vs. New York Mets
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 12:10 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Shea Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV/Radio: Fox Sports South.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: LHP Denny Neagle (9-7, 3.30; 4-3,
4.33 lifetime vs. Mets) vs. RHP Masato Yoshii (4-4, 3.65; 0-1, 3.00
lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Neagle likes this place. He is 4-2 lifetime at Shea with
an ERA of 2.70 during 12 appearances. His career road ERA
everywhere else is 3.87. And that includes his last start in New
York on the last day of the 1997 season, when he gave up five runs
in five innings. This is his first appearance against the Mets this
season. Neagle has won just once in his last three starts, despite
giving up just five earned runs in his last 20 innings. His run
support has dried up. In his last five starts, the Braves have
managed just one run twice and were shut out when he faced the
Yankees on June 16. The league appears to have caught up with the
Mets' Yoshii. The 33-year-old rookie went 4-1 during his first nine
starts but has gone 0-3 in his eight starts since. The Braves beat
him 4-1 on July 4th at Turner Field (6 IP, 7H), although half of
the Braves' runs were unearned. Like Hideo Nomo, he has developed a
recent problem with the strike zone, walking 16 men in his last 28
1/3 innings.
</P>
