<SLUG> BC-BKO-BRUNNER-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TRIAL DATE SET IN BRUNNER ROBBERY CASE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BILLY WITZ  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   A Sept. 11 trial date was set Tuesday for Kenny Brunner, the
former Georgetown basketball player, after he pleaded not guilty to
charges he robbed Los Angeles City College basketball coach Mike
Miller of $1,500 and attempted to murder him.
</P>
<P>
   Brunner, who is being held in L.A. County jail on $550,000 bail,
will have a pre-trial hearing on July 28, at which time his
attorney, Jerome Bradford, is expected to ask Superior Court judge
James Dunn that the charges be dismissed.
</P>
<P>
   Dunn on Tuesday also ordered LaDale Lunnie, who was charged with
robbery in the case, to stand trial. Lunnie told police he helped
Brunner with the robbery, in which Brunner is accused of pointing a
gun at Miller in his LACC office and firing it. The gun, however,
did not go off.
</P>
<P>
   Brunner, a point guard, was a high school All-American at
Dominguez High in Compton. He started as a freshman for Coach John
Thompson at Georgetown before leaving abruptly in midseason. He
later transferred to Fresno State but left after he was suspended
upon being charged in a robbery in Fresno.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
