often a ``tipoff to a ripoff,'' the Federal Trade Commission says.
But the agency doesn't recommend banning it. Instead it says
companies sending such junk e-mail should be prohibited from trying
to disguise its content or origin, which would allow people to
better filter their incoming messages. By NICOLE TSONG. (Already
filed; also filed in ``f'' category)
