<P>
   &QL; 
BOX-BOXING (Los Angeles) _ Day 2 of the three-part boxing series.
Bobby Chacon, 46, has the mentality of a small child. A look into
the eyes of once-charismatic Jerry Quarry, 53, his sister says
sadly, and ``no one is home.'' And who can forget the startling
image of Muhammad Ali, 56, shaking uncontrollably as he tried to
light the Olympic flame in Atlanta in 1996? This, as much as rich
lore and rich purses, is the legacy of boxing. This cannot be
denied: Boxing leads the way in chronic brain damage, an
all-too-overlooked reality that turns too many robust men into
living, breathing zombies.
</P>
<P>
   Which raises the question: Is it time to ban the sport? &QL; 
By Michael Rosenthal. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
