``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOMBING-SUSPECT (Atlanta) _ After five and a half months in
hiding, the man wanted for the bombing of an Alabama abortion
clinic emerged from the woods of western North Carolina last week,
took a large amount of food and a pickup truck from a residence,
and then abandoned the truck and vanished once more, federal
authorities say. By Kevin Sack. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET in
``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ The stock market rallies sharply as several
companies reported good or better-than-expected earnings for the
second quarter, easing concerns about the drag from Asia's economic
turmoil. By Jonathan Fuerbringer. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET
in ``f'' news file.)
