<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-NIGERIA-OBASANJO-NYT, which
moved in ``i'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Look at what has become of this country. We are one of the
world's biggest producers of oil, and we have no fuel. We have more
power stations than we need, and no electricity. Madness.''
</P>
<P>
   _GEN. OLUSEGUN OBASANJO, former president of Nigeria.
</P>
