<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, JULY 15
</HEADLINE>
  Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-TINABROWN-MEDIA-NYT (moved on Sunday, July 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, July 12,
about jury decisions against news organizations referred
incorrectly to a Federal appeals judge's ruling in a lawsuit
against ABC as a result of a hidden-camera report about a Chicago
eye clinic on ``Primetime Live.''
</P>
<P>
   The judge upheld a lower court's dismissal of claims of fraud,
trespass and illegal wiretapping lodged by the eye clinic and two
doctors. ABC was never found liable for fraud and trespass in the
case.
</P>
<P>
   BC-JAPAN-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Sunday, July 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, July 12,
about possible successors to Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto of
Japan misstated the year in which President Bush fell ill during a
state dinner in Tokyo with Prime Minister Kiichi Miyazawa, whom
some consider a possible emergency replacement for Mr. Hashimoto.
It was 1992, not 1993.
</P>
<P>
   BC-POLITICAL-BRIEFS-NYT (moved on Sunday, July 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, July 12,
about this year's Senate race in Missouri misidentified the
recipient of a $200 campaign donation from Mayor Emanuel Cleaver of
Kansas City. He was Attorney General Jay Nixon, not Senator
Christopher S. Bond.
</P>
<P>
   BC-U.N.-RAPE-TRIBUNAL-NYT (moved on Wednesday, July 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, July 8,
about a proposed international tribunal for war crimes cases
misstated the number of cases in which rape has been charged at
another tribunal, the one in The Hague dealing with war crimes in
the Balkans. It is four, not one.
</P>
</TEXT>
