<HEADLINE>
RICHTER TO RETURN TO THE RANGERS 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   In a sudden turn of events Tuesday night, Mike Richter, the
unrestricted free-agent goaltender, reached agreement with the
Rangers on a four-year contract.
</P>
<P>
   Returning to the team for whom he has played the last nine
seasons, Richter got a new contract from the Rangers after it
seemed that the team might sign Curtis Joseph, another prominent
free-agent goalie who had played for Edmonton.
</P>
<P>
   Richter's deal will average between $5.4 million and $5.5
million per season. It is considerably more than the $3.9 million
the goalie made last season. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
