<P>
   (NYT5) BALLYMONEY, Northern Ireland -- July 14, 1998 --
NIRELAND-FUNERAL-1, 7-14 -- As a bell tolls mournfully, the small
coffins of Richard, Mark and Jason Quinn Q three boys born to a
Catholic mother who were being raised as Protestants Q are carried
into a rural Roman Catholic church Tuesday by friends and family,
their faces contorted with grief. The people of Northern Ireland
said a tear-filled farewell to three young brothers burned to death
in a sectarian attack that came as they slept. (Carlos
