A5214 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BRAVES-MAIN15-COX     07-14 0476
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BRAVES-MAIN15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Smoltz in top form as Mets fall
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ No elbow specialist can forecast just how John
Smoltz's elbow with endure the rest of summer of '98. Tuesday
night, that elbow spoke up on its own behalf.
</P>
<P>
   In some of his most impressive work of the season, Smoltz won
for the third time in five starts since coming off the disabled
list, beating the Mets 4-2 in the first of two games at Shea
Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Smoltz (7-2) allowed two runs on a Todd Hundley soft liner in
the third that bounced out of Andruw Jones' glove as he
crash-landed. But that was all he allowed them (six hits, two
walks, six strikeouts) before Kerry Ligtenberg worked the ninth for
his 11th save.
</P>
<P>
   Chipper Jones drove in a pair of with a third-inning double and
a fifth-inning solo homer, his 24th of the year. The win was the
fourth in four games with the Mets this year.
</P>
<P>
   The Braves avoided tying their longest losing streak of the
season, although Smoltz pitched with a bit of history on his side.
The Braves' rotation had not gone 0-4 in consecutive road starts
since Aug. 2-5, 1990, when Tom Glavine, Smoltz, Charlie Leibrandt
and Steve Avery all lost in sequence.
</P>
<P>
   Chipper Jones increased Atlanta's lead to 4-2 with a solo home
run in the fifth inning, his 24th of the year and the fourth of his
career in 28 career at-bats against Mets starter Bobby Jones. That
gave Jones six homers in his last 10 games and leaves him six shy
of setting a career high.
</P>
<P>
   Smoltz helped himself in the fourth when, with men on second and
third, he slapped a hanging 2-2 curveball into right to score Javy
Lopez for a 3-2 lead. The RBI was Smoltz's fourth in just 20
at-bats. He did not help himself one batter later, however, when
Walt Weiss sent a soft liner to second, where Carlos Baerga caught
it and threw to first to double-up Smoltz and end the inning.
</P>
<P>
   John Olerud singled and Mike Piazza doubled with two out in the
third inning, but Smoltz appeared to have escaped the inning when
Hundley lifted a shallow flare into center. Andruw Jones gloved the
ball in a lurch but it popped out when he hit the ground, bringing
both men in and tying it 2-2.
</P>
<P>
   Stringing together a pair of two-out shots in the top of the
third, the Braves went up 2-0. With Weiss on first after a walk,
Chipper Jones hit a deep ball to the opposite field that eluded
catcher-turned-left fielder Hundley and bounced hard off the wall.
Weiss scored easily on Jones' double, his 10th extra-base hit of
the month, and right there it might have stopped.
</P>
<P>
   But when Andres Galarraga next lined a ball to right, Butch
Huskey misjudged how hard it was hit and wound up making a feeble
back-handed reach as the ball skipped past him.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
